gumboot tea
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:basic tea made with black tea leaves which are dried longer than green tea leaves, are darkened as they oxidise, with little blending and without additives.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Usually served with  milk.
